metadata.name: Sleep Paralysis
metadata.description:
35% of the world's population has experienced sleep paralysis at least once.

Many people see creepy, smoke-like creatures screaming or whispering in their ears. People hear sounds similar to wind.

Sleep paralysis is caused by (jinns) genies - intelligent beings from a parallel world, created from pure fire. Sometimes they can come into our world, where we can see them between stages of wakefulness and sleep.

I have tried to recreate sleep paralysis in 3D as much close to that I have experienced and strugled for years by myself.

Have you experienced sleep paralysis?

if you haven't experienced that spooky moment, then now you can find out how it happens.

P.S.: Turn the sound on
